#frida stuff
frida-server*
__handlers__
friTap.egg-info
dist/
*.pcap
*.txt
*.trace
tlslib_research/ # research for certain TLS implementations
tlslib\_research/
site/
*.md
*.sh
*.yml
*.js
*.json
dev/changelog_backfill.py
research/

# Project-tracked files that the broad *.md / *.yml rules above would
# otherwise hide. Keep this list in sync with files that must ship.
!RELEASING.md
!compat.yml
!CONTRIBUTING.md
!.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md
!.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/
!.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/*.yml
# dev/ shell scripts: the broad *.sh rule above hides them, but they are
# part of the maintainer toolchain (compile_agent.sh is invoked by the
# agent-build-check CI job; entrypoint.sh is referenced by dev/Dockerfile).
!dev/*.sh
# scripts/ shell tooling (the public/private tiering leak guards): verify_public_build.sh
# and check_public_denylist.sh (CI leak-guard job) must be tracked despite *.sh above.
!scripts/*.sh
!CHANGELOG.md
!README.md
# requirements-minimal.txt (the lean-install pin set) is a NEW *.txt file the
# broad *.txt rule above would hide; it must ship (MANIFEST.in includes it and
# the docs reference it). Existing tracked *.txt (requirements.txt, private.txt,
# scripts/private_terms.txt) predate the rule, so they need no negation.
!requirements-minimal.txt
# docs/ markdown pages: the broad *.md rule above hides newly-added pages from
# CI's fresh checkout, which breaks `mkdocs build --strict` (nav references not
# found). Keep the whole docs/ tree trackable.
!docs/**/*.md
!docs/*.md
test.json

# Testing artifacts
tests/coverage_html/
tests/coverage.xml
.coverage
.pytest_cache/
test_*.log
*.prof
*.dat

# Development environment
venv/
env/
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json

# npm stuff
# package-lock.json is checked in: agent-build-check (CI) runs `npm ci`
# which requires it. Keep this in sync with the toolchain pin in
# package.json — see RELEASING.md.
!package-lock.json

